# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Policy: the repo carries everything needed to REPRODUCE the work (inputs,
# NNP potential files, scripts, changelog, curated results: CSVs + MAQAO
# reports) and nothing bulky that a run REGENERATES (trajectories, energies,
# restarts, plots, logs, raw run directories).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Results tree: ignore raw run output by default...
results/**
# ...but keep directories visitable so the exceptions below can apply,
!results/**/
# keep every curated CSV (scaling, figS4 panels, power-law fits),
!results/**/*.csv
# and keep the MAQAO ONE View reports in full (html/js/css/svg assets).
!results/maqao/**

logs/
diffusion/

# Massive CP2K per-run output (regenerated by any run)
*.xyz
*.restart
*.restart.bak*
*.ener
*.stress
*.wfn

# NNP parameter files are ignored in run directories (they are copies)...
*.data
# ...but the canonical potentials needed to run the NNP are kept
# (this now also covers potentials/oneill-nacl-water-2024/models/**/*.data):
!potentials/**/*.data

# NaCl training/validation datasets (251 MB) stay out of the repo;
# potentials/oneill-nacl-water-2024/PROVENANCE.md records the upstream commit.
potentials/oneill-nacl-water-2024/data-sets/

# Tar files
*.tar

# Compiled binaries (just in case)
*.psmp
*.exe
*.o
*.mod

# Plots (regenerated by plots/*.py); MAQAO report assets are exempted by the
# results/maqao rule above, which comes later in match order for that path.
*.png
*.pdf
*.svg
!results/maqao/**/*.svg

# NNP data symlinks/folders inside the scaling run directories
**/mpi*_omp*/NNP
**/N_*/NNP

# .out files are KEPT (benchmark/validation outputs are small and cited in
# the reports); per-run giants are already excluded by the results/** rule.
